description: Hell on Earth continues and it's up to Danica and Maggie to put a stop to it. But how do you defeat the living embodiment of evil? How can you possibly defeat Lucifer?
While the Thunderbolts core team wraps up their mission at Gothenvald Castle, the B-team of Mr. Hyde, Boomerang, Shocker, Centurius and Troll is in training with Songbird, Techno and Mach-V.
name: None Shall Survive the Incarsicus!

volume.name: Just Imagine: Mildly Microwaved Pre-Pubescent Kung-Fu Gophers

description:
The Rocketeer Flies Again! Dave Stevens unveiled the Rocketeer nearly 30 years ago to instant acclaim, and in all the years since that auspicious debut, respect for Dave’s talent and his greatest creation have only continued to grow.

Last year, IDW had the honor of releasing the complete Rocketeer saga in several editions, showcasing the work of this great artist as it was always meant to be seen-completely remastered, with nearly every page scanned directly from the originals and recolored by Dave’s hand-picked colorist.

Today we are able to celebrate Dave’s talent once again, with an all-new Rocketeer anthology miniseries written and drawn by some of the finest creators in comics, and with the full cooperation of the Stevens family.

The first star-studded issue of The Rocketeer features a gorgeous cover by Alex Ross, and terrific stories by John Cassaday, Mike Allred, Kurt Busiek, and Michael Kaluta, plus outstanding pin-ups by Mike Mignola and Jim Silke-all paying tribute to the continued legacy of Rocketeer and Dave Stevens!
name: The Rocketeer; Home Again; Dear Betty

description: Spider-Man and Paladin serve as Misty Knight's field agents tracking down the destination of a shipment of the dangerous Atlantean drug, "Hook".
name: Neighborhood, Part 2

description:
FEAR ITSELF TIE-IN! FEAR ITSELF has made its way to Hercules' home turf! Stripped of his powers, Herc must change everything he knows about being a hero to win the day. But against an army of monsters and super villains, what chance does a mere mortal have? Find out when Herc shows the world the true measure of a superhero in Herc #3!

Fear Itself tie-in! Herc foils a bank robbery in progress; the perpetrators all recent escapees of The Raft.
name: Fear Itself

description:
The Darkest Tale of The Darkness Yet!

Apocalypse has come to Ginsberg, CA! Two ominous powers arrive in town, one of ultimate light and the other of deepest darkness, and Jackie Estacado is trapped between them. The Four Horsemen are ascending to their full power. Can Jackie muster the power to prevent the end of the world?

Eclipso's master plan is revealed at last! But how can even he achieve such an outrageous goal? And how does it hinge on his control of the moon and the Emerald City of the Starheart? The JLA must fight Eclipso's ever-growing Shadow Army while looking for answers in a race against time to prevent The End of Days while he targets the next pawn in his plan of ultimate control: The Spectre. Plus, Obsidian is back...but whose side is he on?
name: Eclipso Rising Part Four: Wrath & Vengeance

description: Princess Lucinda's orgins are finally revealed as we learn what exactly happened on her home world and why her and her sister Millicent ended up on Earth.
As Black Lightning's team battles Geo-Force's team, Batman emerges from the shadows. And all are left wondering: Who is Veritas?
name: Who Handles the Truth?

description: To save Mei from her vampire curse, John Sargent sets out to destroy the infamous Shang-Ji. His first stop: Club G-Boss, nightclub, casino and notorious vampire hangout. But after being bitten himself, Sargent is forced to contend with a curse of his own.
name: Book 2

description: Karen Starr has big plans to get Starrware back up and running, involving the media, Africa and Bruce Wayne. But when a terrorist shows up in Gotham City she must put aside her day job – again! – so Power Girl and Batman can save the day! Unfortunately for them, this "terrorist" is a metahuman, and while Power Girl may not remember it, their paths have crossed before.
name: We Can Be Heroes, Part 1.

description: While newly elected Mayor Sharp is the public face of Arkham City, the secret manipulator behind the scenes is the nefarious Dr. Hugo Strange. Sharp presents the walled encampment as Gotham's ultimate solution to crime, but Strange has a secret, darker agenda. He's recruiting his own security force--one that will answer only to him and whose ultimate goal is the death of Batman.
name: Chapter One: Hugo Strange

description:
Overview

Hawkeye, blinded and facing his most deadly foe yet, must make a decision that will change the course of his life! The defining chapter of the Avenging Marksman is here!
name: The Beginning

description:
Trapped in a dangerous world of monsters from Hindu lore, The Teen Titans are being hunted down. Will Superboy be the next to fall? And for what dark purpose does the Demon King Rankor need our heroes? Don't miss the next chapter of Solstice's first adventure with the team!

With Wonder Girl, Ravager, Red Robin and Helena Sandsmark captured by Rankor, Kid Flash races to their rescue but he too is captured.

Meanwhile, Solstice, Beast Boy, Raven Superboy, and a demon disguised as Ravager continue to try to find their captured team mates. The Demon-Rose tricks Superboy into kissing her and then lures him into an ambush by Khara. Beast Boy, Solstice and Raven try to help Superboy but Raven is also overpowered and Demon Rose and Khara make an escape with unconscious Superboy and Raven.

Now with Superboy and Raven caged Rankor is powerful enough to escape the Island of the Demon Kingdom he is trapped on.
name: How the Mighty Fall

Sixteen million mutants dead...and that's just the first step in Cassandra Nova's genocidal plans. With an army of evolved Sentinels primed for annihilation, Nova will stop at nothing to see every mutant exterminated from the planet. Led by Professor Xavier, the X-Men have always sought an end to the ongoing strife between mutants and humans - hoping to one day unite the two species in peaceful coexistence. But the time for dreams is past. Now, their entire existence is under direct attack. Now, it is time for the X-Men to fight.

Collecting NEW X-MEN #114-117 and ANNUAL 2001.
name: Book 1

description: With Deadpool AWOL, Bob has no choice but to take on the mission of rescuing "Blind Al" himself, in Deadpool's costume. And predictably, he botches things and is taken hostage by Al-Qaeda fringe group, The Crescent Moon Knights.
name: One Night in Bangkok

description: Mitsu meets two new clients, both lonely in their unique ways. Meanwhile, his work ethic catches the eye of other employers. Sohta, already overqualified for his job at the power plant, gets demoted due to nepotism and channels his frustration toward the surface of the earth. Another day, another dollar for the workforce of Saturn Apartments.
name: Vol. 3

description: Shizuo's in trouble. At least, his father is convinced he is. In his ongoing campaign to convince his layabout, forty-something progeny to finally get his act together, Shizuo's father suggests a new approach: maybe Shizuo should just treat manga as a hobby and do something else--anything else--so as to look like less of a reject to both his family and society at large. Can Shizuo's burning desire to create manga triumph over his seemingly bottomless capacity for self-doubt and existential angst? Then again, maybe if Shizuo just comes up with a catchy pen name, everything will be golden and he'll quickly find himself on the merry road to publication. Right?
name: Vol. 3

description: UK comic based on the 1980's toyline.

For the final course of Gente, a senator pondering a political maneuver arrives at an unexpected conclusion over a delicious meal at Casetta dell'Orso. A notorious playboy finds himself enthralled by the sophisticated Savina, a Cassetta regular. Lorenzo finally reaches the point in life where he needs glasses, and silent Gigi accepts an invitation from a young lady. Enjoy the dolce conclusion to this charming story.
name: Vol. 3

description: Niarudi and the DRF rule the strange cordlike world of the Recreator. Yet without Eon Green, Niarudi will never be able to remake the world as she wishes. Now the biomechanical inhabitants of the Recreator are beginning to succumb to dronification, a result of the N5S plague that wiped out the original Earth. Only Zoichi and Fuyu can stop the nightmare from repeating itself, but to do so they'll need to find Eon Green and the incredible secret she holds about the past that will shape the future. The final confrontation is at hand, and the prize for victory is the power to transform humanity and the world itself!
name: Vol. 6

description: UK comic based on the 1980's toyline.

Kick-starting the second arc of the hit new series, this issue shines a spotlight on the original Iron Maiden! What ties does this classic foe of the original team have to the current lineup? All we know for sure is that the new Dynamo better watch out, because she sure enjoyed causing the old one pain! Action and intrigue abound in this perfect jumping-on point for new readers!
name: On Victoria

description:
A 2-part comic which is included in the manual of the game.
Jennifer Simpson is a child from the Granite Orphanage in Romsdalen, Norway. She and her friends, who are also orphans (Laura, Ann and Lotte) are adopted in September 1995 (the same month the game was released) by a wealthy recluse named Mr. Barrows and are picked up from the orphanage and taken to the mansion by his wife. They live in a mansion known as the "Clock Tower", named after its most predominant feature, and the girls are under the impression that it will be their future home, or so they thought...
name: Prologo

When his only friend, Brian, the brains and charm of their two-man operation, convinces Alec to help him with a hit contract on a mayoral candidate his life unravels to rock bottom. But sometimes we need to hit rock bottom to begin the climb towards a better day

But Batman insists that you can't change the past, and, well, Batman is kind of always right, so . . . hello, eternal darkness? Cullen Bunn (The Sixth Gun) and ChrisCross bring "Sorcerer Kings" to a sun-shattering conclusion!

Paul Duval , the Grey Gargoyle, reflects on his life as a supervillain while at a cafe in Paris. From his first battles with Thor and Iron Man, to taking on the entire Avengers (and Daredevil) only to be defeated by the Black Knight and the Wasp, and his most recent humiliations from the Sentry and, once again, Thor. He ponders if he is doomed to be a third -rate villain unworthy of the Avengers' attention. And then an object comes crashing down from the sky.....
name: The Worthy: Gargoyle

Seeking justice for the deaths of CENSORED, SNAKE EYES heads to the top of the world and the Himalayan fortress of Rajah Vikrim KHALLIKHAN-a COBRA COMMANDER CANDIDATE! With only Agent Helix, Iceberg and Alpine by his side, Snake Eyes storms the miles-high refuge, confronting his most skilled foes: CENSORED & CENSORED!

name: Jekill!

description:
How many times can you kill a man? The Black Widower, a serial killer

arrested and sentenced to death, comes out of his grave once, twice, three times in seek of revenge.

Dylan has to deal with a ghost or with a murderer with many lives?
name: Ossessione

description:
After an epic disaster is inflicted on Metropolis, Superman works to pick up the pieces – literally. But can he overcome his concern over Lois's disappearance? And as Brainiac and Luthor regroup, their plans start to coalesce in a surprising direction as the war for the future begins!

Lex Luthor has just had the Justice League Watchtower dropped on him and he is near death and he blames Superman. Superman however has bigger things on his mind. Brainiac has stolen the Daily Planet, with everyone still inside, and taken it off world.

While Superman and the rest of the world's heros look for Brainiac and ship, Luthor goes on the operating table to save his life, but just as the doctor is about to begin Brainiac kidnaps Luthor and takes him to his ship. Once on board Brainiac saves Luthor's life and against his will gives him robotic limbs. Luthor still not trusting Brainiac demands that Brainiac help him release the Daily Planet and make Luthor look the hero he always wanted to be.
name: Reconstruction

description: A young woman is scared by the darkness monster she feared as a child. It comes during the thunderstorm, when electric light fades. And it's determined to kill. Only Dylan Dog can believe her, and he is the right one for this sort of mystery.
name: Il buio
